  "glossaryTerms": [
    { "slug": "pumpkin-puree-note", "term": "pumpkin puree", "definition": "Tinned pumpkin puree is cooked and strained pumpkin, sold in 400–425 g tins. It has the texture of thick fruit puree. Not to be confused with pumpkin pie filling, which is pre-sweetened and already spiced. For this recipe, use plain pumpkin puree." }
  ],
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          { "type": "text", "text": "The bread gets its distinctive moist crumb from the " },
          { "type": "text", "marks": [{ "type": "glossaryTooltip", "attrs": { "termSlug": "pumpkin-puree-note" } }], "text": "pumpkin puree" },
          { "type": "text", "text": ", which contributes both water and pectin. It bakes low and slow for an hour — the interior stays dense and moist while the crust sets and cracks along the top in the usual quick-bread way." }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": { "title": null },
            "content": [
